    <div id="weedlib" class="tab-pane">
        <h2><i class="fas fa-leaf"></i> Weed Library · Identification & Resources (Photos Coming)</h2>
        <p><span class="weed-badge declared">Declared Weed</span> = Legally required to control · <span class="weed-badge environmental">Environmental Weed</span> = Threat to native ecosystems</p>
        <p><strong>For current control methods and herbicide recommendations, follow the NRE Tas links below each weed.</strong></p>

        <div class="weed-grid">
            <!-- Declared Weeds -->
            <div class="weed-card"><img src="weeds/gorse.jpg" alt="Gorse" onerror="this.src='https://placehold.co/400x300/e9ecef/495057?text=Gorse+-+Add+photo'"><div class="weed-card-content"><span class="weed-badge declared">Declared Weed</span><h4>Gorse (Ulex europaeus)</h4><p><strong>Key ID:</strong> Dense spiny shrub, bright yellow flowers (winter-spring), seed pods explode when ripe.</p><p><strong>Habitat:</strong> Roadsides, pasture, bushland, coastal areas.</p><a href="https://nre.tas.gov.au/agriculture/weeds/weeds-index/gorse" target="_blank" class="weed-link"><i class="fas fa-external-link-alt"></i> NRE Tas control guide</a></div></div>
            <div class="weed-card"><img src="weeds/montpelier-broom.jpg" alt="Montpelier Broom" onerror="this.src='https://placehold.co/400x300/e9ecef/495057?text=Montpelier+Broom+-+Add+photo'"><div class="weed-card-content"><span class="weed-badge declared">Declared Weed</span><h4>Montpelier Broom (Genista monspessulana)</h4><p><strong>Key ID:</strong> Soft green leaves, yellow pea-flowers (spring), flat seed pods with hairs.</p><p><strong>Habitat:</strong> Roadsides, bushland, disturbed areas.</p><a href="https://nre.tas.gov.au/agriculture/weeds/weeds-index/montpelier-broom" target="_blank" class="weed-link"><i class="fas fa-external-link-alt"></i> NRE Tas control guide</a></div></div>
            <div class="weed-card"><img src="weeds/ragwort.jpg" alt="Ragwort" onerror="this.src='https://placehold.co/400x300/e9ecef/495057?text=Ragwort+-+Add+photo'"><div class="weed-card-content"><span class="weed-badge declared">Declared Weed</span><h4>Ragwort (Jacobaea vulgaris)</h4><p><strong>Key ID:</strong> Yellow daisy flowers, deeply lobed leaves, toxic to livestock.</p><p><strong>Habitat:</strong> Pasture, roadsides, disturbed areas.</p><a href="https://nre.tas.gov.au/agriculture/weeds/weeds-index/ragwort" target="_blank" class="weed-link"><i class="fas fa-external-link-alt"></i> NRE Tas control guide</a></div></div>
            <div class="weed-card"><img src="weeds/pampas-grass.jpg" alt="Pampas Grass" onerror="this.src='https://placehold.co/400x300/e9ecef/495057?text=Pampas+Grass+-+Add+photo'"><div class="weed-card-content"><span class="weed-badge declared">Declared Weed</span><h4>Pampas Grass (Cortaderia selloana)</h4><p><strong>Key ID:</strong> Large fluffy white/pink plumes (summer), sharp-edged leaves, grows 2-4m tall.</p><p><strong>Habitat:</strong> Roadsides, cliffs, logged areas, coastal.</p><a href="https://nre.tas.gov.au/agriculture/weeds/weeds-index/pampas-grass" target="_blank" class="weed-link"><i class="fas fa-external-link-alt"></i> NRE Tas control guide</a></div></div>
            <div class="weed-card"><img src="weeds/boneseed.jpg" alt="Boneseed" onerror="this.src='https://placehold.co/400x300/e9ecef/495057?text=Boneseed+-+Add+photo'"><div class="weed-card-content"><span class="weed-badge declared">Declared Weed</span><h4>Boneseed (Chrysanthemoides monilifera)</h4><p><strong>Key ID:</strong> Yellow daisy flowers (winter-spring), fleshy black berries, toothed leaves.</p><p><strong>Habitat:</strong> Coastal areas, roadsides, bushland.</p><a href="https://nre.tas.gov.au/agriculture/weeds/weeds-index/boneseed" target="_blank" class="weed-link"><i class="fas fa-external-link-alt"></i> NRE Tas control guide</a></div></div>
            <div class="weed-card"><img src="weeds/blackberry.jpg" alt="Blackberry" onerror="this.src='https://placehold.co/400x300/e9ecef/495057?text=Blackberry+-+Add+photo'"><div class="weed-card-content"><span class="weed-badge declared">Declared Weed</span><h4>Blackberry (Rubus fruticosus agg.)</h4><p><strong>Key ID:</strong> Prickly arching canes, white/pink flowers, black berries (summer).</p><p><strong>Habitat:</strong> Creeksides, roadsides, pasture, bushland edges.</p><a href="https://nre.tas.gov.au/agriculture/weeds/weeds-index/blackberry" target="_blank" class="weed-link"><i class="fas fa-external-link-alt"></i> NRE Tas control guide</a></div></div>

            <!-- Environmental Weeds -->
            <div class="weed-card"><img src="weeds/capeweed.jpg" alt="Capeweed" onerror="this.src='https://placehold.co/400x300/e9ecef/495057?text=Capeweed+-+Add+photo'"><div class="weed-card-content"><span class="weed-badge environmental">Environmental Weed</span><h4>Capeweed (Arctotheca calendula)</h4><p><strong>Key ID:</strong> Yellow daisy flowers with dark centre, silver-grey lobed leaves, prostrate rosette.</p><p><strong>Habitat:</strong> Pasture, roadsides, disturbed areas.</p><a href="https://weeds.org.au/profiles/capeweed/" target="_blank" class="weed-link"><i class="fas fa-external-link-alt"></i> Weeds Australia profile</a></div></div>
            <div class="weed-card"><img src="weeds/banana-passionfruit.jpg" alt="Banana Passionfruit" onerror="this.src='https://placehold.co/400x300/e9ecef/495057?text=Banana+Passionfruit+-+Add+photo'"><div class="weed-card-content"><span class="weed-badge environmental">Environmental Weed</span><h4>Banana Passionfruit (Passiflora tripartita var. mollissima)</h4><p><strong>Key ID:</strong> Climbing vine, pink tubular flowers, yellow banana-shaped fruit, velvety leaves.</p><p><strong>Habitat:</strong> Rainforest edges, roadsides, gullies.</p><a href="https://weeds.org.au/profiles/passiflora-mollissima/" target="_blank" class="weed-link"><i class="fas fa-external-link-alt"></i> Weeds Australia profile</a></div></div>
            <div class="weed-card"><img src="weeds/spear-thistle.jpg" alt="Spear Thistle" onerror="this.src='https://placehold.co/400x300/e9ecef/495057?text=Spear+Thistle+-+Add+photo'"><div class="weed-card-content"><span class="weed-badge environmental">Environmental Weed</span><h4>Spear Thistle (Cirsium vulgare)</h4><p><strong>Key ID:</strong> Purple flower heads, spiny winged stems, deeply lobed spiny leaves.</p><p><strong>Habitat:</strong> Pasture, roadsides, disturbed areas.</p><a href="https://weeds.org.au/profiles/spear-thistle/" target="_blank" class="weed-link"><i class="fas fa-external-link-alt"></i> Weeds Australia profile</a></div></div>
            <div class="weed-card"><img src="weeds/cotoneaster.jpg" alt="Cotoneaster" onerror="this.src='https://placehold.co/400x300/e9ecef/495057?text=Cotoneaster+-+Add+photo'"><div class="weed-card-content"><span class="weed-badge environmental">Environmental Weed</span><h4>Cotoneaster (Cotoneaster glaucophyllus)</h4><p><strong>Key ID:</strong> Evergreen shrub, small white/pink flowers, red berries, glossy leaves.</p><p><strong>Habitat:</strong> Bushland, roadsides, rocky outcrops.</p><a href="https://weeds.org.au/profiles/cotoneaster/" target="_blank" class="weed-link"><i class="fas fa-external-link-alt"></i> Weeds Australia profile</a></div></div>
            <div class="weed-card"><img src="weeds/mirror-bush.jpg" alt="Mirror Bush" onerror="this.src='https://placehold.co/400x300/e9ecef/495057?text=Mirror+Bush+-+Add+photo'"><div class="weed-card-content"><span class="weed-badge environmental">Environmental Weed</span><h4>Mirror Bush (Coprosma repens)</h4><p><strong>Key ID:</strong> Shiny dark green leaves, orange-red berries, dense growth habit.</p><p><strong>Habitat:</strong> Coastal areas, roadsides, bushland edges.</p><a href="https://weeds.org.au/profiles/coprosma-repens/" target="_blank" class="weed-link"><i class="fas fa-external-link-alt"></i> Weeds Australia profile</a></div></div>
            <div class="weed-card"><img src="weeds/sweet-pittosporum.jpg" alt="Sweet Pittosporum" onerror="this.src='https://placehold.co/400x300/e9ecef/495057?text=Sweet+Pittosporum+-+Add+photo'"><div class="weed-card-content"><span class="weed-badge environmental">Environmental Weed</span><h4>Sweet Pittosporum (Pittosporum undulatum)</h4><p><strong>Key ID:</strong> Dark green wavy leaves, cream flowers (spring), orange berries with sticky seeds.</p><p><strong>Habitat:</strong> Wet forests, gullies, urban bushland.</p><a href="https://weeds.org.au/profiles/pittosporum-undulatum/" target="_blank" class="weed-link"><i class="fas fa-external-link-alt"></i> Weeds Australia profile</a></div></div>
